description:
        Clio is more than just a tech company–we are a global leader that is transforming the legal experience for all by bettering the lives of legal professionals while increasing access to justice .

We’re looking for an Assistant Controller to join our Finance team. This role is available to candidates remotely across Canada (excluding Quebec) and the USA.


What your team does:


Our Finance team is hyper-focused on becoming one of the most high performing teams in the world. That means we work hard, play for keeps, and dedicate ourselves to making sure #TeamMoney thrives as we scale. You will be joining a high performing and hard-working team that values having fun at work. We strive to meet our deadlines, but as with all accountants - we worship balance as well. Your position will be an integral part of the team.


What you’ll work on:



 Oversee the financial operations of the Company and its subsidiary corporations, including the design of an organizational structure adequate for achieving the team’s goals and objectives, and contributions to the monthly accounting cycle, such as approving high value journal entries; 

 Oversee the design, implementation, and operating effectiveness of a robust system of SOX-compliant Internal Controls over Financial Reporting; 

 Maintain a documented system of accounting policies and procedures governing workflows and internal controls; 

 Oversee the Company’s treasury policies and procedures, including cash management, accounts payable review and execution, and monitoring the A/R cycle; 

 Manage relationships with bankers and other vendors; 

 Identify and execute on opportunities to drive efficiency, accuracy, and impact across all aspects of the accounting and financial operations aspects of the Company, including improvements to process involving our tools, such as Netsuite; 

 Administer the Company’s Capitalization Table and Stock Option Plan, including ensuring appropriate withholdings from option exercises as applicable; 

 Prepare technical accounting memos evaluating material transactions recurring and ad-hoc transactions of the Company; 

 Assist with the review and oversight over compliance and timely reporting of all income and sales taxes; 

 Coordinate preparation of external consolidated financial statements and corresponding working papers and schedules; 

 Coordinate preparation of external quarterly reporting to the board and other external stakeholders, including contributing to management’s discussion and analysis; 

 Oversee the external audit, including liaising with external auditors, responding to audit queries, preparing audit working papers as appropriate, and ensuring the timely completion of all audit procedures; 

 Contribute operationally to the growth of the Company; 

 Mentor and lead team members and help to grow the Finance team to support organizational needs; 

 Work directly with the Controller, Accounting Manager, and CFO to scale the financial operations at the Company; 

 Ad hoc reporting and other duties, as required. 




What you might have:



 7+ years of experience of full cycle accounting or auditing in a Sarbanes-Oxley controls environment; 

 Exposure to and enjoyment of full cycle accounting process ; 

 Ridiculous attention to little details; 

 The ability to wow people with your concise written and verbal communication skills; 

 A track record of organization; 

 Experience managing and overseeing a small team and cross-departmental projects; 

 Experience working in an office environment; 

 Special tricks and techniques for multitasking effectively; 

 Solid understanding of accounting fundamentals, specifically US GAAP; 

 Excellent MS office skills (Excel, Word, PowerPoint); and, 

 A CPA designation 




Diversity, Inclusion, Belonging and Equity (DIBE) &amp; Accessibility 


Our team shows up as their authentic selves, and are united by our mission. We are dedicated to diversity, equity and inclusion . We pride ourselves in building and fostering an environment where our teams feel included, valued, and enabled to do the best work of their careers, wherever they choose to log in from. We believe that different perspectives, skills, backgrounds, and experiences result in higher-performing teams and better innovation. We are committed to equal employment and we encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply.

Clio provides accessibility accommodations during the recruitment process. Should you require any accommodation, please let us know and we will work with you to meet your needs.

Learn more about our culture at clio.com/careers


About Clio


At Clio, we are on a mission to transform the legal experience for all. As the world's leading provider of cloud-based legal software, we provide lawyers with low-barrier, affordable solutions to manage and grow their firms more effectively, more profitably, and with better client experiences. Through the cloud, we believe that we can help create a more inclusive legal community and a more equitable legal system. We are an award-winning team that has been recognized as one of Canada’s Best Managed Companies , Canada’s Most Admired Cultures and has topped Fast Company’s list of Most Innovative Companies . In line with our mission, we’ve been up to some big things, including becoming a multi-product company, launching a $1 million COVID-19 Legal Relief Initiative , and most recently, securing a US$110M Series E funding round and a USD $1.6B valuation. This is a historic moment in the growth of legal technology! As the first legal practice management unicorn globally, and one of only a handful of Canadian unicorns, this is only the beginning. If you’ve ever wanted to do the best work of your career, while having a meaningful impact in the lives of others, then Clio is the place for you.

