About Clio


At Clio, we are on a mission to transform the legal experience for all. As the world's leading provider of cloud-based legal software, we provide lawyers with low-barrier, affordable solutions to manage and grow their firms more effectively, more profitably, and with better client experiences. Through the cloud, we believe that we can help create a more inclusive legal community and a more equitable legal system. We are an award-winning team that has been recognized as one of Canada’s Best Managed Companies , Canada’s Most Admired Cultures and has topped Fast Company’s list of Most Innovative Companies . In line with our mission, we’ve been up to some big things, including becoming a multi-product company, launching a $1 million COVID-19 Legal Relief Initiative , and most recently, securing a US$110M Series E funding round and a USD $1.6B valuation. This is a historic moment in the growth of legal technology! As the first legal practice management unicorn globally, and one of only a handful of Canadian unicorns, this is only the beginning. If you’ve ever wanted to do the best work of your career, while having a meaningful impact in the lives of others, then Clio is the place for you.

        If you are interested in growing your proven accounting skills and experience, one of our accounting positions in Banff, Revelstoke or Canmore could be the perfect way to propel your career!

Baker Tilly Rockies LLP is looking for candidates to fill our Accounting Technician and Staff Accountant positions. These candidates will have recent accounting experience to contribute to our Firm in delivering the primarily accounting, tax and the wide range of business advisory services we provide. At BTR we have been providing public accounting, tax and entrepreneurial support services to the Bow Valley for over thirty years, and have expanded to open quickly growing offices in Revelstoke, BC and Innisfail, AB. We are passionate about the clients we serve and the quality of our work, thus we put significant importance to finding the right accounting professionals to join our team. We foster a professional working environment, as well as the time, resources and knowledge to support and grow our valued staff all the way up to partnership. We service very diverse business communities which provide our staff with interesting experiences in all aspects of accounting, taxation, audit and business consulting with a vast number of industries and complexity.


Flexible work weeks that allow you to set your own schedule so long as monthly full-time standard hours are worked (no core hour requirement);

Overtime bonuses, no required overtime and the option to bank overtime for future time off;

Spring 2022 start date;

Competitive compensation package including group extended health care benefits, life and disability insurance, employee assistance program, and health trust fund;

Continuing Professional Development courses covered to maintain your designation as well as numerous in-house courses, and informal training and development opportunities.


Your primary responsibilities will include:




Skills



With consistent challenge in the level of work, you will develop your skills in

In our tax focused firm, you will primarily prepare Notice to Reader reports, and corporate and personal income tax returns, all while ensuring time budgets and file deadlines are met.


Understanding client’s business, identifying and resolving accounting and tax issues;

Adding value to our existing clients on engagements and their business in general;

Creating time efficiencies and managing multiple deadlines;

Contributing to the maintenance of our positive team dynamic with all levels of staff and management.


A successful candidate will have:



Recent public practice Firm work experience (preferred);

Sound knowledge of tax compliance (an asset);

A working knowledge of Caseware Financials, Taxprep, and QuickBooks (an asset);

Effective communication skills;

Technical skills in tax and advisory services, specifically in corporate and personal income tax return and Notice to Reader preparation (an asset);

A dedication to client service;

A desire to share knowledge, and continously learn throughout your career with BTR.


Application Information:




If You Are Looking To Take The Next Step To Grow Your Career In Our Informal, Fun, And Development Rich Public Practice Firm, Please Email a PDF Of Your Resume, Unofficial Transcripts And Cover Letter Indicating Why You Want To Live In The Banff, Canmore Or Revelstoke Region To



Leigh-Anne Finch

Human Resources Manager

lcfinch@bakertilly.ca

Manager, Finance 



Toronto – Job #5390






Who we are:





Canaccord Genuity (CG) is a leading independent full-service financial services firm, with operations in two principal segments of the securities industry: wealth management and capital markets. CG is driven by an unwavering commitment to build lasting client relationships – we achieve this by generating value for our individual, institutional, and corporate clients through comprehensive wealth management solutions and investment banking services. We are a leading independent wealth management firm in Canada, and the leading mid-market provider of investment banking advisory, equity research, sales and trading services for corporations and institutions.




We pride ourselves on understanding our clients’ needs and finding innovative, bespoke solutions. Our entrepreneurial and friendly team will challenge you to learn and grow every day. We value great work and collaboration and strive to eliminate bureaucratic thinking. We’re looking for talented people who thrive in a fast-paced environment and want to have an impact with innovative ideas and best practices.




Come be a part of our Canadian success story and help deliver superior experiences for our clients. At CG, we recognize that diversity across our business strengthens our client relationships and enables more innovative solutions. We strongly encourage applications from all qualified individuals regardless of race, religion, colour, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, or disability status. CG provides an accessible candidate experience. If you need any accommodations throughout the interview process and beyond, please let us know.




Our Canadian operation, Canaccord Genuity Corp., is currently looking for a Manager, Finance to join our Finance team in Toronto.





Responsibilities:






Responsible for daily/monthly P&amp;L reporting, P&amp;L and Balance Sheet analysis and providing commentaries;

Perform various Account Reconciliations and posting Accounting entries;

Manage, facilitate and coordinate specialized projects relating to financial planning and analysis, management reporting, and public reporting;

Prepare monthly operating reports for management including development and analysis of performance metrics and review of budget variances;

Prepare and maintain group budgets, forecasts, capital plans and cash flow projections;

Work closely with senior management in Finance and various business units and auditors to provide financial insight and reports in connection with special projects and ad hoc analyses;

Complete reports and projects in accordance with established policies and guidelines accurately, timely and efficiently;

Proactively seek continuous enhancement in internal controls over financial transactions and financial reporting;

Be a key asset within the Finance team, with proficiency in excel, and various systems and applications;

Ad-hoc analysis and support as requested by management;









Skills &amp; Qualifications:






Bachelor’s degree in Accounting or Finance; CFA/CPA holder or actively working towards an accounting designation preferred;

Advanced Microsoft Excel and Power Point skills are essential;

5+ years of experience in financial/accounting analysis in a large organization. Experience in a Finance/Accounting role at a broker-dealer firm will be preferred;

Demonstrated ability to meet deadlines and work under pressure;

An effective ability to collect, organize, analyze and circulate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy;

Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with ability to interact with all levels of the organization;

Self-motivated with a focus on driving results and strong sense of accountability;

Experience with Dataphile accounting software is an asset.

Analyste financier corporatif – Consolidation et conformité



English version will follow










Le défi de l’analyste financier corporatif – Consolidation et conformité en quelques mots : 



Leader mondial dans le domaine des tests et de la qualité, Averna fournit des solutions et des services de test de pointe aux fabricants d'appareils électroniques et de communication du monde entier, accélérant ainsi le développement, la qualité et l'innovation des produits de ses clients - dont de nombreux 
Global 1000
 - dans de nombreux secteurs. Ce qui a commencé comme une entreprise de trois personnes en 1999 est aujourd'hui une organisation multinationale couvrant 8 pays, avec plus de 400 employés et d'innombrables succès et récompenses.




Nous recherchons un analyste financier corporatif – Consolidation et conformité pour se joindre à notre équipe des Finances qui relèvera du 
Directeur Principal – Rapport financiers, conformité et contrôles. L’analyste financier 
sera responsable de la consolidation mensuelle du Groupe, de la mise en application de la stratégie de prix de transfert et d’assurer la conformité des entités canadienne et américaine auprès des différentes législations fiscales. L’analyste financier corporatif participera également à la préparation des provisions d’impôts, à l’amélioration de la gestion de la trésorerie ainsi qu’à plusieurs projets spéciaux.




Nous recherchons un candidat avec un intérêt marqué pour la comptabilité complexe et voulant approfondir ses connaissances en fiscalité. Ce poste permettra au candidat choisi de s’impliquer dans des sujets variés dans un environnement en pleine croissance et stimulant.




Ne laissez pas passer cette opportunité de mettre en œuvre votre leadership et votre proactivité pour améliorer continuellement nos processus et faire la différence chez Averna !











Votre contribution dans ce rôle : 



Effectuer la consolidation mensuelle des résultats de la société-mère et de ses filiales, incluant le rapprochement et l’élimination des transactions interco et de l’enregistrement des recharges inter-régions et des écritures de consolidation et coordonner la consolidation des filiales de la société-mère ;

Participer à la préparation du dossier trimestriel et annuel des provisions d’impôts futurs et actuels et de la documentation support à remettre aux consultants externes pour la préparation des déclarations de revenus ;

Maintenir le rapprochement des comptes de Grand Livre d’impôts ;

Mettre en application la stratégie de prix de transfert du Groupe ;

Maintenir le calendrier des rapports requis par les autorités fiscales au Canada et aux États-Unis pour les taxes de vente, l'impôt sur les sociétés, et autres demandes de conformité et coordonner la préparation de la documentation à l'appui ;

Évaluer les besoins d’enregistrement des entités canadiennes ou américaines dans de nouvelles juridictions fiscales ;

Participer à la préparation de la documentation fiscale lors de l’enregistrement dans une nouvelle juridiction et partager ces informations aux parties prenantes internes ;

Analyser et participer à l’optimisation de la gestion de la trésorerie et préparer les rapports de position de la trésorerie pour la haute direction ;

Coordonner les règlements en espèces de soldes d'Interco, et autres initiatives de trésorerie ;

Coordonner la comptabilité de l’entité japonaise ;

Participer au processus de renouvellement annuel des assurances du Groupe ;

Participer à la préparation des dossiers annuels d’audit ;

Soutenir le Directeur Principal – Conformité et la Contrôleur Corporatif dans des initiatives
ad hoc
 ;













Le candidat idéal en quelques mots : 



Détenir un titre professionnel comptable (
CPA
) ou être en voie de l’obtenir ;


3-5 ans d'expérience
 en 
comptabilité dans une société multinationale et multidevise
 ;

Expérience et/ou intérêt marqué pour la 
fiscalité des entreprises canadienne, américaine et internationale
 ;

Expérience en matière de 
consolidation
 ;

Expérience à répondre et s'adapter à de nouvelles exigences en matière comptables, légales et/ou fiscales ;

Capacité démontrée à respecter des 
délais serrés
 ;

Capacité à s’adapter et grandir dans une entreprise en évolution ;

Capacité d’effectuer des tâches multiples en continue ;

Être autonome et aimer résoudre des problèmes ;

Connaissance intermédiaire de 
Excel
 ;

Expérience avec un ERP, 
D365
 un atout ;


Bilingue
 - Parler et écrire couramment l'anglais et le français. L’espagnol, un atout.









Ce que nous VOUS offrons
 :


Une rémunération globale compétitive

Des avantages sociaux complets

Un jour de congé supplémentaire pour votre anniversaire










Averna fait partie des Sociétés les mieux gérées au Canada









La diversité fait partie des valeurs et des engagements d’Averna. L'utilisation du genre masculin a été adoptée afin de faciliter la lecture et n'a aucune intention discriminatoire.

























































Corporate Financial Analyst - Consolidation and Compliance 







The Corporate Accountant Challenge - Consolidation and Compliance in a few words


: 





A worldwide Test &amp; Quality leader, Averna delivers industry-leading test solutions and services for communications and electronics device makers worldwide, accelerating product development, quality, and innovation for clients - including many Global 1000s - across many industries. What started as a three-person company in 1999 is now a multinational organization spanning 8 countries, with over 400 employees and countless successes and awards.




We are looking for a Corporate Financial Analyst - Consolidation and Compliance to join our Finance team that will be reporting to the Senior Director - Financial Reporting, Compliance and Controls. The Financial Analyst will be responsible for the monthly consolidation of the Group, the application of the transfer pricing strategy and ensuring the compliance of the Canadian and US entities with the various tax legislations. The Corporate Financial Analyst will also participate in the preparation of tax provisions, the improvement of cash management and several special projects.




We are looking for a candidate with a strong interest in complex accounting and who is interested to further his or her knowledge in taxation. This position will allow the chosen candidate to get involved in various subjects in a growing and stimulating environment.




Don't miss this opportunity to apply your leadership and proactivity to continuously improve our processes and make a difference at Averna!











Your contribution in this role: 



Perform monthly consolidation of the parent company and its subsidiaries, including the reconciliation and elimination of interco transactions and the posting of inter-region recharges and consolidation entries, and coordinate the consolidation of the parent company’s subsidiaries ;

Participate in the preparation of the quarterly and annual future and current tax provision file and supporting documentation to be provided to external consultants for tax return preparation;

Maintain the reconciliation of tax ledger accounts;

Put in effect the Group's transfer pricing strategy;

Maintain the schedule of required fillings by the Canadian and American tax authorities for sales tax, corporate tax, and other compliance requests and coordinate the preparation of the supporting documentation;

Evaluate the need for registration for the Canadian or US entities in new tax jurisdictions;

Participate in the preparation of tax documentation upon registration in a new jurisdiction and share this information with internal stakeholders;

Analyze and participate in the optimization of cash management and prepare cash position reports for senior management;

Coordinate cash settlements of Interco balances, and other treasury initiatives;

Coordinate the accounting of the Japanese entity;

Participate in the Group's annual insurance renewal process;

Participate in the preparation of the annual audit files;

Support the Senior Director - Compliance and Corporate Controller in ad hoc initiatives;

















The ideal candidate in a few words: 



Hold a professional accounting designation (
CPA
) or be in the process of obtaining one;


3-5 years of accounting experience
 in an 
international multi-currency company
;

Experience and/or strong interest in Canadian, US and international corporate taxation;

Experience in consolidation;

Experience in responding and adapting to new accounting, legal and/or tax requirements;

Demonstrated ability to meet tight deadlines;

Ability to adapt and grow in a changing business;

Ability to multi-task continuously;

Ability to work independently and enjoy problem solving;

Intermediate knowledge of 
Excel
 ;

Experience with an ERP, 
D365
 an asset;


Bilingual 
- Fluent in English and French. Spanish is an asset.












What's in it for YOU



Competitive total compensation

Full benefits

An additional day off for your birthday










Averna is one of Canada's Best Managed Companies
